&lt;p&gt;Recent studies have demonstrated oligodendroglial involvement in pathological pathways in Alzheimer&amp;#39;s disease, however on a descriptive level only. We address these yet unexplored pathological mechanisms, by using post-mortem human brain tissue samples, human iPSC-derived model systems in combination with modern transcriptomic approaches with the aim to study how Alzheimer-related stress affects oligodendrocyte health and function.&lt;/p&gt;

